Complete the Mission:

Synopsis: You are a captured soldier of the Undergrave Army within the confines of the Resinfaire State. Due to the
damage sustained from the surprised attack, you have amnesia. The only memory that remains: "Complete the Mission".

Berlin Interpretation Values:
1. Random Dungeon Generation
2. Permadeath
3. Turn-Based
4. Non-Model - Movement, battle and other actions take place in the same mode. Every action is available at any point in
               the game.
5. Emergent Game Systems - Allow several solutions to common goals. Item/monster or item/item interactions.
6. Resource Management - Stamina, Hunger, Thirst, limited item capacity
NO. 7. Hack and Slash - Player vs world, no diplomancy
8. Exploration and Discovery


Core Mechanic - Stealth
    - Visible FOV
        - By "focusing/wait" Player can view all FOV of every unit within Player's FOV and move accordingly.
        - All NPCs are "Facing" a direction and cannot see behind them or far to their sides.

    - MGS Alert/Evasion/Caution Modes
        - UI Mode
            - UI of Player will be red/yellow/light yellow depending on current mode
        - Alert Mode
            - Player is spotted and enemies have sounded alarm bell. Stronger enemies will appear from lower/upper
              levels to assist.

        - Caution Mode
            - Player is spotted and current encounter is engaging Player. Enemies will call for help or to alarm bell if
              unable to suppress Player or threat

        - Evasion Mode
            - Player has successfully evaded being seen after initial encounter, the area of last sighting will have
              patrols causing the dungeon level to be more difficult to pass through.

    - Lighting Mechanics
        - More lit areas allow NPCs to have full FOV, dark areas reduce NPC FOV

    - Sound Graphics
        - All units has a "FOH"(Field of Hearing) that allows unit to "hear" visually in unexplored areas or areas out of
          FOV.
        - Player has a naturally higher FOH
        - All "sounds" will have a graphic if outside of Player FOV
